  "title": "Hierarchical Menu - showParentLevel works only for immediate parent",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\nWhen the `showParentLevel` prop is set to `true`, the Hierarchical Menu widget is only showing sibling categories of the selected category.\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://instantsearchjs.netlify.app/stories/?path=/story/refinements-hierarchicalmenu--default\r\n2. Click on `Appliances`\r\n3. Click on `Fans`\r\n4. Click on `Ceiling Fans`\r\n5. Categories list is only showing `Fans` categories\r\n\r\n<!-- A live example helps a lot! Fork the sandbox, reproduce the bug and paste the URL here: -->\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe expected behavior is that the Hierarchical Menu widget shows sibling categories on all levels, as per comment in the https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/master/src/widgets/hierarchical-menu/hierarchical-menu.tsx#L128\r\n\r\n## 🖥 Screenshots\r\nSecond level category selected:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6537892/169808083-a8af8b62-270f-4d5e-8881-08e09eea9466.png)\r\n\r\nThe third level category selected, all parent categories` siblings are hidden:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6537892/169808209-fc044348-f832-4f9a-beef-886fecede7ab.png)\r\n\r\n<!-- If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem. -->\r\n\r\n\r\n## Additional context\r\nThe same bug is also reproducible in `react-instantsearch`, https://react-instantsearch.netlify.app/storybook/?path=/story/hierarchicalmenu--default\r\n<!-- Add any other context about the problem here. -->\r\n",
